		<main id="main" class="site-main" role="main"><article id="post-104" class="post-104 page type-page status-publish hentry"><header class="entry-header"><h1 class="entry-title">Home of the Trojans</h1>	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-content">
		<p><a href="http://ndsa.portal.airast.org/secure-browsers.stml"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-2399 size-full" src="http://www.tlm.k12.nd.us/files/2016/10/School-pic-e1521745795234.jpg" alt="School pic" width="618" height="369"></a></p>
<div data-contents="true">
<div class="" data-block="true" data-editor="btt99" data-offset-key="a0gev-0-0">
<h3></h3>
<h3>Order Your 2019-2020 Yearbook!</h3>
<h3><a href="http://www.tlm.k12.nd.us/files/2020/04/Screen-Shot-2020-04-15-at-4.00.57-PM.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-3873" src="http://www.tlm.k12.nd.us/files/2020/04/Screen-Shot-2020-04-15-at-4.00.57-PM-297x300.png" alt="screen-shot-2020-04-15-at-4-00-57-pm" width="297" height="300"></a></h3>
<h3>Attendance Procedure:</h3>
<p>Teachers will continue to take attendance for all classes according to parameters teachers have set up and communicated with students and/or parents. This might be something as simple as being counted present for being present for an online check-in. We also will be running grade reports every Monday and sending out letters to the parents of children who are lagging behind. The point is not to be punitive, but rather make sure all students are keeping up with their studies. Read the Covid-19 Update below for more details.</p>
<h3>April 3rd, 2020 :</h3>
<h3><a href="http://www.tlm.k12.nd.us/files/2012/10/April-3-2020-Covid-19-Update.docx">Covid-19 Update</a></h3>
<h3><strong>Turtle Lake – Mercer Distance Learning Plan – Approved 3/30/2020</strong></h3>
<h3><strong><a href="http://www.tlm.k12.nd.us/files/2012/10/TLM-Remote-Learning-Plan-FINAL.docx">Turtle Lake – Mercer Distance Learning Plan</a></strong></h3>
<h3><strong>BOYS LOCKER ROOM<br></strong></h3>
<p>Dear parents,</p>
<p>Please review the <a href="http://www.tlm.k12.nd.us/files/2020/03/Boys-Lockers.pdf" target="_blank">attached document </a>to identify your student’s belongings. Boys did not turn in their locker numbers to their phy ed instructor and/or coach. School personnel emptied these lockers and put them in bags, labelling the bags with the locker number. You will notice some bags have names on them, you will want to verify these are your student’s belongings. Arrangements may be made for pickup by emailing Steven.Heyd@k12.nd.us or calling the school at 448-2365. Please include the following information:</p>
<p>• Date and Time you want to pickup<br>
• Photo Number<br>
• Student Name<br>
• Phone Number for call back</p>
<p>We apologize for the inconvenience this may have caused.</p>
<p>Sincerely,<br>
Steve Heyd<br>
Principal, Turtle Lake Mercer Public School</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>NOTICE FOR ELECTION FILING FOR CANDIDACY TO HAVE NAMES PLACED ON THE SCHOOL BOARD ELECTION BALLOTS:<br></strong></p>
<p>Residents who desire to be on the ballot for the school board election being held on Tuesday, June 9, 2020 must file a statement that includes the candidates name and the specific position being sought along with a financial disclosure statement.  This must be filed before <strong>4:00 p.m</strong>., <strong>April 6, 2020</strong> with Susan Davis, Business Manager, at the Turtle Lake-Mercer School, Turtle Lake, North Dakota.  <strong> The financial disclosure form and statement of candidacy form may be obtained from Business Manager Susan Davis by appointment by calling 1 701-448-2365 Extension 103 or 1-701-351-7647 in Turtle Lake</strong>.</p>
<p>Please return the forms before the deadline using one of the following methods:</p>
<p><strong>Appointment by calling 1-701-448-2365 Extension 103 or 1-701-351-7647.<br></strong></p>
<p><strong>E-mailed to <a href="mailto:susan.davis@k12.nd.us">susan.davis@k12.nd.us</a>.  Please keep in mind the deadline for filing is before 4:00 p.m., April 6, 2020. All e-mails must be sent accordingly to be accepted.  Please call me to let me know you sent the e-mailed documents so I can make sure I receive it.  </strong></p>
<p> </p>
